snippet.textDisplay: I dont think most people understand the offside rule, Arms arent considered as a playing body part, there has to be 2 players in between the player and goal line, in Salah's case the goal keeper was behind him so they had to check for the last defender, Mane's hips were off, offside line was drawn correctly(watford 2nd last defender's toe against mane's hips). All var decisions were correct, i forgot to mention if you look at mane from a different angle he is easily a few inches off, its just they had to use that angle we saw so they could draw the lines. My question is what was VAR supposed to do here, with respect to the rule book how could they rule it a goal, they have to go by the laws written by the FA, cant give subjective decisions otherwise that would be against fairplay.
